{"number":28,"title":"LinkedIn post","body":"Priority: High\n\nDue: Friday (June 12)\n\nContent:\n\nWe don&#39;t just tell clients how to use AI. We run our own company on it.\n\nThis month we made our entire organization queryable through AI: our data warehouse, financials, CRM, time tracking, meeting notes, and codebase, all connected in one place.\n\nA few things that now run on autopilot:\n\n- A weekly business overview with pipeline movement, project status, and spend, compiled for us.\n- A daily briefing that researches our upcoming calls, preps the docs, and drafts context-aware follow-up emails for contacts due in the CRM.\n- Automated CRM updates and follow-up drafts after every client call.\n- Month-end financials and reporting, plus analytics on demand.\n\nThe point isn&#39;t the tooling. It&#39;s that we&#39;d never recommend a workflow we haven&#39;t put our own operation through first.\n\nIf you&#39;re trying to figure out how AI can help your business, that&#39;s a conversation we love having. Book a free discovery call. Link in the comments.\n","state":"OPEN","labels":["priority:high"],"created_at":"2026-06-09T22:47:35Z","updated_at":"2026-06-09T23:01:20Z"},
